The Office of International Relations (OIR) was constituted in 1998. 

Since the inception, OIR has been overseeing all the international programs of the Institute, including:

Exchange/visiting programs for students, faculty and researchers for the cooperation in education and research;

Admission of the international students to various academic programs of the Institute [e.g., B.Sc. (research), M.Tech. (course and research) and Ph.D.];

Visits of the international academic and diplomatic delegations to the Institute, the Institute’s delegations to foreign universities to strengthen our existing collaborations and to forge new partnerships. 

Formulation and execution of MoU's and agreements between IISc and institutions abroad

